.TH "platform_device_add_data" 9 "platform_device_add_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
platform_device_add_data \- add platform-specific data to a platform device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" platform_device_add_data
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ","
.BI "const void *data "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
platform device allocated by platform_device_alloc to add resources to
.IP "data" 12
platform specific data for this platform device
.IP "size" 12
size of platform specific data
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add a copy of platform specific data to the platform device's
platform_data pointer.  The memory associated with the platform data
will be freed when the platform device is released.
